description:
Subjects Addressed: From Horeb, the Lord gave spiritual drink and the Ten Commandments. We must preach the righteousness of Christ, preach Christ in the Law. (19:45)
The spiritual drink represents the dew and the rain (the former and latter rain) that we must receive before the Time of Trouble. (25:00)
The Hebrews were attacked at Rephidim, which represents the Sunday Law crisis. (32:00)
The Hebrews were attacked by Amalek, which represents the Mark of the Beast crisis and the Time of Trouble. (38:00)
February 2016, Warmest Month On Record. World Has More Reasons To Take On Climate Change and enforce Sunday observance. (47:30)
John Kerry, the United States House of Representatives agree with Pope Francis that ISIS’ killings is Genocide. An international army is being set up to fight “fundamentalists.” (51:06)
Pope Francis: Religions and nations must unite to fight “fundamentalists,” those who believe in absolute truth. (1:02:00)
King Saul’s final test came when he encountered the Amalekites. However, David overthrew the Amalekites. (1:05:00)
As long as the hands of Moses were uplifted, victory came to the Hebrews in the battle with Amalek. SDAs are lowering God’s standards. (1:18:00)
